<div id="pro-tip" style="width: 70%;">
        <br>
        Find man pages by section:

        <p>
        <code>
            apropos -s 3 printf
        </code>
        </p>

        <p>
            Apropos will restrict its search to
			<a href="https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/3586/what-do-the-numbers-in-a-man-page-mean">the manual section</a>
			given.
        </p>

        Option Summary:
        <ul style="list-style: none; margin: 0; padding: 0">
            <li><code><b>-s</b> <u>list</u>, <b>--sections</b> <u>list</u>, <b>--section</b> <u>list</u></code>
				<br>
				Search only the given manual sections.  <br>
				<u>list</u> is a colon- or comma-separated list of sections.
			  </li>
        </ul>
        <br>
		Source: <a href="http://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man1/apropos.1.html"><code>apropos(1)</code></a>
		<br><br>
    </div>
